prj:ScienceGoal.prj:note:
With an uniform Herschel-selected sample of potential distant galaxies,  we will be able to: (i) obtain an unbiased census on the SFR density of the Universe at intermediate redshifts (z~3); (ii) derive the distribution of dust temperatures in IR luminous galaxies including the most extreme objects; (iii) define a reliable sample of very high redshift star-forming galaxy candidates which will be ideal targets for further ALMA follow-up in CO transition lines;
(iv) obtain a systematic assessment and characterization of confusion and blending problems in the longest Herschel bands. Given that large beams and the background fluctuations by 
undetected sources are a major issue for Herschel, digging into the confusion of the Herschel images is fundamental to optimize the multi-wavelength identification of sources, and torefine the existing SED libraries.
